<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-22T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="915" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d915">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/5–2247: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-22T18:00:00-04:00">May 22, 1947—6
                                p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>608. To Adler from Treasury. Authorize compromise omission of reference to
                        “both parties” or “either party,” preferring, however, inclusion following
                        in exchange of letters: “arrangement is subject to review by both parties
                        from time to time in light of changing circumstances.” If necessary to reach
                        agreement authorize acceptance Chinese position on this point.
                        [Treasury.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>